Q: There are ten lime soda bottles on a table in a restaurant. They are to be served among two different groups of customers consisting of 5 members each. How many ways are there to create these 2 groups?
Options: (a) 90 (b) 105 (c) 126 (d) 252 (e) 525
A:
 We can choose 5 from 10 to be in the first group. The remaining 5 will be in the second group. So the answer is 10C5 = 10 * 5 = 50. So the answer is (d).

